************************************************************************************
+                                                                                  +
+                       Tiny Robot Navigation System                               +
+                          			                                     +
+                                                                                  +
************************************************************************************

This software alows the the tiny robot to navigate within a table of units 5 x 5



prerequisites:
-------------

Pleasemake sure that the following softwares are installed in your OS of choice:

1) GIT
steps to install is available at : https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-Installing-Git

2) Python 3.x 
follow the link to install python: https://python.land/installing-python



Follow the Steps to run the software:
-------------------------------------
1) clone the repo from github
   git clone https://github.com/kbcbals/challenge.git
2) cd challenge
3) python3 main.py



System Initialization:
----------------------
  It is important to run the menu and choose the item '1. List input files' for the system to build the database of the input files.

In terminal:
  python3 main.py 

select the option '1. List input files'




Features :
----------

The menu structure looks like this:

     Menu List:
           1. List input files  
           2. Input File Number to load
           3. Create default input file
           4. Stats
           5. Exit/Quit 


selection 2:
------------ 
will allow the use to choose the input file to load for testing the system


The sample output for selection item 2:
--------------------------------------
What would you like to do? 2

 Enter input file number to test : 10 <---- this is the number of the file listed , when the files are listed in 'System Initialization'

Output: 0,1,NORTH
Total execution time=0.203 milliseconds
--------------------------------------


selection 3:
------------ 
will allow the use to create a default input file. It will be available in the current folder.
using this file, the user can create input files to be inputted to the system



The sample output for selection item 2:
--------------------------------------

What would you like to do? 3

 Please enter the name of input file :  sample

--------------------------------------


selection 4:
------------ 
This is feature of the system which will give information as to the average time consumed 
for running the jobs, number of jobs run , the max and min time consumption jobs (with job names)


The sample output for selection item 4:
--------------------------------------
some cool Stats:
----------------
  Number of jobs run :8
  average time [ job exec time] : 0.0329  milliseconds
Job execution times:
  maximum : 0.553  milliseconds, input file name : place-cmd.inp
  minimum : 0.177  milliseconds, input file name : input4.inp

--------------------------------------
                                                     


selection 5:
------------ 
Exit / Quit the system



